- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant because the paper aims to capture polynomial time, which is a central concept in computational complexity theory. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant because the paper mentions the application of the results to database theory. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible because cographs (graphs that are the complement of a disjoint union of cliques) have connections to geometric intersection graphs.
